reviews.text:
Well bundled layers with cohesion&#xD;
&#xD;
Lightly starchy with a puddingesque mouth feel. Lightly sweet base and pretty much on-point to my own homemade rice pudding. Steeped 12 days while it traveled in the mail from recipe creator. The carmel butter floats around with a perfectly balanced flavor adding obvious butter to the base and a bright authentic well caramelized top layer tone. Throat hit is smooth considering how well toasted to top layer is. Just beautiful.&#xD;
&#xD;
This is one very authentic rice pudding. Alternatively I am also getting a "French Toast" vibe from it as well. Which means you could pick at the mid layer and get somewhere with a French Toast.&#xD;
&#xD;
Brought this around to a local vape shop and the most common two descriptors were "On-point" and "Authentic"&#xD;
&#xD;
